are found throughout asia; momos, mandu, gyoza, and jiaozi are all basically variations of the same thing. baozi (包子), steamed buns stuffed with savoury, sweet or vegetable fillings. mantou (馒头), steamed bread available on the roadside - great for a very cheap and filling snack. lanzhou-style lamian (拉面), fresh hand-pulled noodles. this industry is heavily dominated by members of the hui (回族) ethnic group[38] - look for a tiny restaurant with staff in muslim dress, white fez-like hats on the men and head scarves on the women. in guangdong and sometimes elsewhere, dim sum (点心). at any major tourist destination 